There are several files in this directory that explore usage of various
system calls/library functions related to memory management:

memory_management handout.pdf: provides brief descriptions of various
memory management related funtions.

process-memory-layout.c: explores the virtual addresses of code, data,
heap and stack segments of a process

brk-explore.c: experiments wit brk() and sbrk()

malloc-explore.c: explores malloc functions

virtual-mem-explore.c: explores getrlimit() and setrlimit()

mmap-example-write.c: explores writing to a file using mmap( ) and munmap()

mmap-example-read.c: explores reading from the files created using the
mmap-explore-write program using mmap( ) and munmap()

To compile: gcc -o <executable-filename> filename

